Text.SourceString: Ommm…//Oh… A new face. Feeling really good vibes from you, mate.
May our paths cross again.
I sell anything. Some of them are rare, you see...//But I don't have a specific category, per se.
You can say that my category is...rare?//<portrait=happy>Maybe...
If you need rare seeds, rare furniture, or a specific item, I might be your guy.//I might have it in my caravan somewhere.
I would definitely sell them to you if I can find it. Check often!
This island is breathtaking.
Sometimes we just need to take a step back and pay attention to our surroundings.
You don't need a lot of money to be happy, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Look at me… I don't have a lot of money, but I'm happy...//<portrait=happy>I've got all I need.
People throw perfectly good items. It's sad to just see them as junk, so I rehome them.
Sell them at a price, yes... Something like that.//You got the idea... Nice!
Umm... Are you a folk type of person? Or more of a mate type?
No need to be so confused, my friend. It's a hard one.//<portrait=normal>Identity is never easy to answer.
I pick up items for <NpcName>Sam</> sometimes.//You know, little things like seeds and stuff... He pays well for delivery.
The beach is the perfect place to forget about life.//<portrait=happy>It fills your brain with waves, birds singing... There is no room for any other thing.
Not even room to think, honestly... Sometimes, I find myself sitting at the beach and...//<portrait=surprised>BAM! Suddenly it's night time.
I grow flowers near the caravan sometimes, to kinda help the bee population.//I also sell some of the flowers that I harvest.
Not always, sometimes, I grow herbs.//<portrait=normal>I don't buy the seeds, just whatever I can find around the island.
I usually stay in my van all day on the weekend.//Cleaning up.
Um… Cleaning up stuff. You know. This and that.//<portrait=annoyed>There’s a lot to clean.
I grow flowers near the caravan sometimes, to kinda help the bee population.//I also sell some of the flowers that I harvest.
Not always, sometimes, I grow herbs.//<portrait=normal>I don't buy the seeds, just whatever I can find around the island.
Ah, <PlayerName>$player</>... <PlayerName>$player</>... Here I am.. And there you are...
I have been wandering around, thinking to myself...//<portrait=happy>Who am I destined to meet on this joyful day...
I'm a wanderer. I don't settle in one spot.//It's just not who I am.
Yes... I have always been a wanderer...//<portrait=normal>Since the age of 3, according to my mom.
I tried boots before. But they just didn't feel right on my feet.
Also, there was this strong odor after wearing it awhile...//<portrait=happy>I took that as my feet telling me no.
Yeah, the caravan works.
Well, the brakes are a little funny sometimes...//<portrait=happy>You gotta kick it real deep, but hey! Aside from that, it rides okay.

Oh Tuesday... Tuesday. Tomorrow is probably Wednesday...//<portrait=concerned>It's all <Italic>so</> predictable. This world needs a twist and a push of creativity.//<portrait=happy>And you know what? Yesterday was indeed Monday.
I like to think that it was meant to be Moon-day. The day of brightness.//<portrait=happy>It was the beginning of the week, which means the day of rejoicing...//Are we getting each other here?
Ah, <PlayerName>$player</>... <PlayerName>$player</>... Here I am.. And there you are...
I have been wandering around, thinking to myself...//<portrait=happy>Who am I destined to meet on this joyful day...
There are many things that you can collect at the beach.
Coconut, shells, shiny shells, dull shells... All kinds of shells.
I think about my duck sometimes...//<portrait=happy>What is going through his mind and all that.//...You know, the usual.
I got a duck from <NpcName>Jack</>, but he's boarding him for me.//<portrait=normal>I think it's best that <NpcName>Funbucket</> lives with his friends than to travel with me. You know...
<NpcName>Funbucket</> is one happy fella.//<portrait=normal>I was gathering fodder for <NpcName>Jack</> when I first saw him running around the yard.
When my store is quiet like this, I think about my duck sometimes...//He lives at the barn over there.
Do you have any pets, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Sandals are the way to go. I'm a no cage kind of guy.//Not on animals, not on my feet.
You know what I'm saying, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Whenever I want, I'm free to see my toes dancing... Now that's something.
I'm a wanderer. I don't settle in one spot.//It's just not who I am.//<portrait=annoyed>Except for today, I guess.
You heard of this thing. Um... Tempeh?
Oh yeah... Those things are yummy as heck.
Trees are a beautiful force of nature. They are who they are and never judge...
It’s true that they can't speak, but that is not the point. The point is us, <PlayerName>$player</>, we are injected with knowledge and stuff. It makes us feel okay to judge one another.
My coffee? Yes, I had it this morning. Why?
Sometimes I visit the ranch to help out with the animals. Also, <NpcName>Jack</> hires me part-time to gather extra fodder.
It's an easy job, and I can use the extra money...
My friend! <PlayerName>$player</>! How are we doing today? The wind is kind to me today, my friend. I can not ask for a better Thursday.
I can try, though. But I'm sure I would fail.
Sometimes time goes fast, and sometimes it goes really slow. Like really really slow...
This time thing isn't for me, my friend. I learned early in life that I am cruising on a different altitude.
I've been trying to pick up a new hobby lately. I do carpentry but not too often... What do you like to do in your free time, <NPCName>Luke</>?
Eerrrr... Sorry. This is awkward...
Names are all jumbled up... Way too many people living here, to remember...... <PlayerName>$player</>, <PlayerName>$player</>. <PlayerName>$player</>...
Visiting the cavern, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I'd be careful in there if I were you. I took my quartz inside the cavern one time... You know, to recharge the vibe...//And I came out with a couple of bats on my hair... Nesting.
You heard of this thing.. Um... Tempeh?
Oh yeah... Those things are yummy as heck... But nothing beats fresh bananas, though.
I'm gonna take a chill day today, <PlayerName>$player</>. See if I can make some money here instead.
My friend! <PlayerName>$player</>! How are we doing today?//The wind is kind to me today, my friend. I can not ask for a better Sunday.
I can try, though. But I'm sure I would fail.
I plant flowers around my caravan sometimes to attract more bees to this island...
Sometimes I visit the ranch to help out with the animals. Also, <NpcName>Jack</> hires me part-time to gather extra fodder.
It's an easy job, and I can use the extra money...
Happy New Year!
You got a trumpet to blow there, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Lots of mushrooms grow on this island, mate.//Hmm… Hang on… Let me list them for you! Shiitake, black trumpet, truffle…
There’s that tiny red one, the poisonous kind.//<portrait=normal>You know, you probably shouldn’t eat it, though…//<portrait=happy>Just to be safe, give them to me.
You seem like the chill farmer type. Not the get-off-my-lawn kind.//<portrait=normal>Know what I mean?
A friend was camping on someone’s lawn one time, and he may have been kicked out.
Fine, fine. Who am I kidding? It was me.//I was the friend who got kicked out.//<portrait=normal>In my defense, it looked like an overgrown cemetery.
What are you planting on your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
It’s been a long day, huh?//<portrait=annoyed>You seem a bit drained…
I’d rest and surround myself with healing quartz if I were you.//<portrait=happy>Just inhaling positivity until my body is overwhelmed by joy.
<PlayerName>$player</>, don’t you just love all the flowers? So much life around us. Let’s stay still for a moment and absorb it all.
I love Spring. I can hear the birds chirping again.//<portrait=happy>Like me! I’m <Italic>chirping</> again. I’M A BIRD!
Do you have any of those fancy-schmancy mushroom logs, <PlayerName>$player</>? They’re pretty cool, but I like to gather mushrooms from the wild. There are plenty around the island right now.
Are you allergic to pollen, mate? The doctor’s been sneezing constantly, and I feel really bad for him.//The doctor with the short hair, not the one with the cool <Italic>green</> hair.
Ah, Spring. Everything is just so beautiful, isn’t it?
Spring mushrooms taste different from Fall mushrooms. Both are delicious, though.
Ah, Summer. Enjoy the heat and humidity, <PlayerName>$player</>. Isn’t it great?
I hear people complaining about the heat, but nah, mate. Just enjoy the heat. Absorb all the good sun.
Nothing really changes much for me in Summer. It’s pretty chill.//Well, actually, it’s pretty hot, but you know what I mean.
Woo! It’s getting hot, isn’t it? But no sweat. We just gotta take more showers, eh?//<portrait=happy>Get it? No sweat?
Sometimes it gets too hot in the caravan, but then I can just head to the tavern or stand in front of <NPCName>Sam’s</> fresh groceries section to cool off.
You hear that Summer music, <PlayerName>$player</>? Pretty awesome, isn’t it?
It’s all right that the grass is a bit patchy, you know? Sometimes nature just needs to do its thing. Doesn’t mean it’s less great.
Am I sad the leaves are falling?//A little bit, but I know they’ll grow back.
Take a deep breath, <PlayerName>$player</>. In…and out… Fill your lungs with that crisp Fall air. Nice, right?
The Fall air always makes me want to travel.
See those red and orange leaves? It means I’m gonna leave town soon.//<portrait=happy>Don’t worry, mate, I’m coming back. So don’t miss me too much.
Ah, too bad I’m leaving soon.//I see all these mushrooms popping up, and I won’t be able to gather any on my trip.
What am I doing on my trip? Oh, this and that.//<portrait=happy>Mostly, I just need to stretch my legs, if you catch my drift.
Ah, Fall. It’s just so beautiful, isn’t it? All the beautiful colors…//Makes me want to head out of town and travel for a while.
I need to start preparing for my trip next week.//<portrait=normal>Let’s see, I need to stock up on mushrooms, green tea…
My trip was great, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s one of the upsides of living in a van – that’s what I call my caravan sometimes. I can take my home anywhere!//But I’m ready to chill here for a while.
<PlayerName>$player</>, let’s take a deep breath of that chilly Winter.//Whoa…THAT IS COLD.//I think my brain froze a little there.
What’s the point of complaining about the cold air? It is what it is, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Besides, look at all that beautiful snow.
It’s kinda chilly, you know? Maybe I’ll head to the tavern to warm up before I go to bed.//This whole town is my home, mate. The tavern, this van…your cabin, eh? Heh heh heh!
You know, once I’m all snuggled up in bed, I don’t really notice the temperature.//It’s kinda nice, actually, to sleep when it’s freezing cold out… As long as I don’t freeze, that’s all I’m asking.

All the snow covering the ground… That’s Winter, mate.//It’s one of the reasons I always come back here for Winter. Who wants to miss out on this beauty?//But also, I don’t have a long-term parking permit anywhere else.
I’ve got a few things to sell at the Winter Fair. Why don’t you stop by and see what I’ve got?
I collected some cool things on my trip. Why don’t you check them out during the Winter Fair? I’ll have a booth there.
You seem like the chill farmer type. Not the "get-off-my-lawn" kind.//<portrait=normal>You know what I'm talking about?
A friend was camping on someone's lawn one time, and he may have been kicked out.
Fine fine. Who am I kidding... It was me.//I was that friend who got kicked out.//<portrait=normal>In my defense, it looked like an overgrown cemetery.
My hair is fine the way it is. We wanna go natural on it.
If they intend to fall, they will fall gracefully.//If they plan to float with humidity, who are we to stop it.
Sandals are the way to go. I'm a no-cage kind of guy. Not on animals, not on my feet.
You know what I'm saying, <PlayerName>$player</>? I'm free to see whenever I want to see my toes dancing. Can we say the same about you, though?
It's been a long day, huh? You seem a bit drained.
I would rest and surround myself with healing quartz if I were you.//Just inhaling positivity until my body is overwhelmed by joy.
Aaaaahhhhhhh.... Say it with me. AAAAAAAAAhhhhh--
I bet you're feeling better already.
I'm heading out about two weeks from now. Need a change in scenery, you know?
I'll be back in the Winter, and I'll bring a bunch of new stuff to sell.
Fall’s been great, but I gotta head out. Change of scenery and all that.//I’m leaving next week.
Nice to see you again, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Great to be back. I should go to see <NpcName>Suki</>.
Aaa... Yeah, and other people too.

<NpcName>Jack</> showed me a picture of <NpcName>Funbucket</> on the animal day, and he looked like he was having the time of his life.//He just walked and walked. Saying hi to everybody... A kind-hearted fellow, that one.
<NpcName>Funbucket</> is my boy!
Did you get any truffles today? I looked around for it this morning and only found a couple.
At this time of year, there should be plenty around the island.
I'm not feeling too jolly today.
Got the blues, I think... Hmm...
It's plenty warm inside the caravan. I have a tiny stove that works as a heater as well.
The space isn't that big, so there isn't much to heat up.//But if I get too cold, I walk over to the tavern and chill the night out.
So much rain lately... Beez...
It's much warmer here during the rain than inside my caravan.
It isn't too bad here during the rain, eh?
I should go back. I'm so sleepy!
Why is it raining so hard lately... Beez...
*mumble to self* Is there a leak in my caravan?
It's much warmer here during the rain than inside my caravan.
It's much warmer here during the rain than inside my caravan.
Beanie sure helps with the snow...
It's plenty warm inside the caravan.//I have a tiny stove that works as a heater as well.
The space isn't that big, so there isn't much to heat up.//<portrait=happy>But if I get too cold, I walk over to the tavern and chill the night out.
It's a nice change to come here after a hot desert music festival.
I think I'm just gonna chill here today.
I can sell you my crystals for some extra good vibes in your cabin.//Just give me the right price...//<portrait=happy>If the crystals agree, they are yours...
The stars are watching us down here, <PlayerName>$player</>...//They are writing us letters, stories that we can only see in our dreams.
All I need in life is green tea and some bananas.//<portrait=happy>They're all I need to spread positivity.
Rose quartz gives all the love...//<portrait=normal>We get love. We give love... You know what I mean...
It isn't too bad living in this thing.//<portrait=happy>The best thing is you can always drive off when you're bored. Hah!
<NpcName>Suki</> taught me how to make green smoothies.//<portrait=annoyed>Want some?
Welcome to my house!
<NpcName>Emily</> cuts my hair. She oozes talent, doesn’t she?//But that's not why I'm here.//I'm here to deliver some stuff for <NpcName>Sam</>.
Hmm... I thought about settling down and opening a store like this...//<portrait=concerned>But between you and me, it isn't really my style though...
Dry rice can last 4-5 years, and they're filling.//So I try to keep a couple of boxes in my van.
Hmm... Should I buy bread or a tortilla?
It's quite a walk to get here, eh? Especially from your place.
One of these days, I'm going to start writing about crystals.
You can mark my word on that! I think it's about time... You know what I mean?
I wanted to park here, but Mayor <NpcName>Connor</> never issued me a permit. Hah!
He was afraid my caravan might damage the festival field.//<portrait=normal>I understand... All cool...
I'm saving all these wild fruits for my lunch tomorrow.
They might still have some, near the inn! Go, grab 'em!
I heard this area isn’t on the town’s original map… The locals built it up years ago because they needed higher ground for the lighthouse.
Would you believe me if I told you I learned that in my dreams?
Well, well, well… Look who’s here…
Trying to get away from the town, huh? You and me both.//What a view.
I like to meditate here. I think it might be my favorite spot…a bit hidden.//Just me and the ocean waves.
Being around animals makes me happy—especially this cute little duck.
<NpcName>Funbucket</> is one happy fella.
Ah, picking up some work, friend. <NpcName>Jack</> hires me part-time to gather extra fodder.
It's an easy job, and I can use the extra money.
